---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Insurance for International Professors | Compare Expat Plans";
const description = "Health insurance guide for Professors working internationally, covering academic positions abroad, research university careers, and global higher education opportunities.";
const headline = "Insurance for International Professors";
const subheadline = "Coverage solutions for Professors working abroad, conducting research internationally, and pursuing academic careers across universities and institutions worldwide.";
const canonicalPath = "/guides/professor-insurance";
const heroBackgroundImage = "/images/guides/professor-insurance-hero.png";

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', label: 'Overview' },
  { id: 'coverage-needs', label: 'Coverage Needs' },
  { id: 'work-settings', label: 'Work Settings' },
  { id: 'credentials', label: 'Credentials' },
  { id: 'occupational-health', label: 'Occupational Health' },
  { id: 'work-demands', label: 'Work Demands' },
  { id: 'career-considerations', label: 'Career Considerations' },
  { id: 'faqs', label: 'FAQs' },
  { id: 'next-steps', label: 'Next Steps' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title={title}
  description={description}
  headline={headline}
  subheadline={subheadline}
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  heroBackgroundImage={heroBackgroundImage}
  tocItems={tocItems}
>
  <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

    <section id="overview">
      <h2>International Professor Careers</h2>
      <p>
        Professors teach at universities, conduct research, publish scholarship, and mentor graduate students. International academic careers offer opportunities to work at prestigious institutions worldwide, collaborate with global research networks, and develop expertise in international academic communities.
      </p>
      <p>
        International academic opportunities exist through universities worldwide, research institutions, visiting professorships, sabbatical exchanges, and the global nature of academic scholarship and collaboration.
      </p>
      <p>
        This guide addresses insurance considerations for Professors working abroad across universities and institutions worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="coverage-needs">
      <h2>Coverage Needs for Professors</h2>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={[
          { key: 'need', header: 'Coverage Need' },
          { key: 'why', header: 'Why It Matters' },
          { key: 'typical', header: 'Coverage Situation?' },
        ]}
        rows={[
          { need: 'General health coverage', why: 'Professional health maintenance', typical: 'Usually university-provided' },
          { need: 'Mental health support', why: 'Academic pressure and research stress', typical: 'Often included' },
          { need: 'Ergonomic coverage', why: 'Research and writing posture', typical: 'Consider including' },
          { need: 'Eye coverage', why: 'Extensive reading and screen work', typical: 'Consider including' },
          { need: 'Travel coverage', why: 'Conference and research travel', typical: 'Often provided' },
          { need: 'Voice care', why: 'Lecturing demands', typical: 'Consider including' },
        ]}
      />

      <h3>Academic Pressure</h3>
      <p>
        Academic careers involve significant pressure—publication demands, grant competition, tenure stress, and balancing teaching with research. These pressures create mental health concerns that benefit from support. Mental health coverage helps manage the competitive nature of academic life.
      </p>
      <p>
        Research and writing involve extended periods of focused intellectual work. Eye strain from reading, ergonomic issues from desk work, and voice strain from lecturing are common occupational health concerns.
      </p>

      <h3>University Benefits</h3>
      <p>
        Universities typically offer comprehensive benefits for faculty positions. International universities vary in benefit quality—established institutions generally provide strong packages. Visiting and adjunct positions may have more limited coverage.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-settings">
      <h2>Coverage by Work Setting</h2>

      <h3>Research University</h3>
      <p>
        Research-intensive institution. Comprehensive university benefits. Research focus. Research universities offer resources.
      </p>

      <h3>Teaching College</h3>
      <p>
        Teaching-focused institution. College benefits. Teaching emphasis. Teaching colleges offer balance.
      </p>

      <h3>Visiting Position</h3>
      <p>
        Visiting professor role. Variable coverage. Temporary appointment. Visiting offers experience.
      </p>

      <h3>Research Institute</h3>
      <p>
        Research-only position. Institute benefits. Pure research. Institutes offer focus.
      </p>

      <h3>Adjunct</h3>
      <p>
        Part-time academic. Limited benefits. Course-based. Adjunct offers flexibility.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Coverage for Professors"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Professors working abroad across universities and institutions worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Professor Plans"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

    <section id="credentials">
      <h2>Credentials and Professional Recognition</h2>

      <h3>Doctoral Degree</h3>
      <p>
        PhD required for professorships. Terminal degree in field. Doctoral qualification essential.
      </p>

      <h3>Publication Record</h3>
      <p>
        Research publications. Journal articles. Books and chapters. Publication validates scholarship.
      </p>

      <h3>Teaching Experience</h3>
      <p>
        University teaching. Course development. Student mentorship. Teaching experience valued.
      </p>

      <h3>Research Grants</h3>
      <p>
        External funding. Grant success. Research support. Grants demonstrate capability.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="occupational-health">
      <h2>Occupational Health Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Academic Stress</h3>
      <p>
        Publication pressure. Tenure stress. Grant competition. Mental health support valuable.
      </p>

      <h3>Sedentary Research</h3>
      <p>
        Extended reading. Writing sessions. Desk work. Ergonomic coverage relevant.
      </p>

      <h3>Visual Demands</h3>
      <p>
        Extensive reading. Screen research. Document review. Eye coverage important.
      </p>

      <h3>Lecturing</h3>
      <p>
        Voice projection. Extended speaking. Teaching sessions. Voice care valuable.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-demands">
      <h2>Managing Work Demands</h2>

      <h3>Teaching</h3>
      <p>
        Course delivery. Student instruction. Lecture preparation. Teaching is core responsibility.
      </p>

      <h3>Research</h3>
      <p>
        Original scholarship. Grant proposals. Research projects. Research advances knowledge.
      </p>

      <h3>Service</h3>
      <p>
        Committee work. Department service. Professional organizations. Service builds institutions.
      </p>

      <h3>Mentorship</h3>
      <p>
        Graduate advising. Student development. Career guidance. Mentorship develops scholars.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="career-considerations">
      <h2>Career Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Global Academic Market</h3>
      <p>
        International positions available. Global scholar mobility. Research collaboration worldwide. Opportunities exist globally.
      </p>

      <h3>Career Paths</h3>
      <p>
        Assistant to associate to full professor. Department chair. Dean. Provost. Academic administration available.
      </p>

      <h3>Tenure Systems</h3>
      <p>
        Tenure systems vary internationally. Contract types differ. Job security varies. Research tenure expectations.
      </p>

      <h3>Research Networks</h3>
      <p>
        International collaboration. Conference participation. Research partnerships. Networks advance careers.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="faqs">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">I'm a professor considering international work. What should I know?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Universities typically provide benefits. Tenure systems vary. Research expectations differ. International experience valued.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do universities provide international coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Most universities yes. Quality varies. Established institutions comprehensive. Verify specific package.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is mental health coverage important?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Yes for academic pressure. Publication stress significant. Tenure anxiety common. Support valuable.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do academic credentials transfer internationally?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Generally yes. Prestigious institutions recognized globally. Publications travel. Academic credentials portable.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What about sabbatical coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Home institution may cover. Visiting institution varies. Verify before sabbatical. Gap coverage may be needed.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What's the career outlook?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Competitive but opportunities exist. STEM fields growing. Higher education expanding globally. Outlook varies by field.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="next-steps">
      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <p>
        Start by evaluating university benefits packages. Consider mental health coverage for academic pressure. Include ergonomic and eye coverage for research work. Verify international coverage scope for your position.
      </p>
      <p>
        Professors advance knowledge worldwide. Your coverage should support academic careers—addressing research and teaching demands, covering health maintenance, and protecting you across academic work worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Protect Your Academic Career"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Professors working abroad across universities and institutions worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

  </article>
</PageShell>
